{
  "doc_id": "47230",
  "text": "MatTek dishes (MatTek Corp, Ashland, MA) at 2 × 10 5 cells / dish and transfected with EB3-GFP plasmid (0.5 μ g) was co-transfected with TTBK1 or pcDNA3.1 + plasmids (0.5 μ g) as described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The live imaging of comet movement of EB3-GFP homodimer was captured 24h later by the following setting: 100× oil objective (NA=1.45), 488 nm excitation (100-300 ms exposure/frame, single plane), 0.53 fps for 40 frames, using the Nikon TE-2000U inverted fluorescent microscope (Nikon Instruments, Melville, NY) output port and cooled charge-coupled device camera (Coolsnap HQ, Roper Scientific, Duluth, GA) as described [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
